      • calculateSimilarity

        public static double calculateSimilarity(ListData[] one,
                                         ListData[] two)
        Calculates the similarity between two pairs of lists. Both parameters are expected to be length two arrays. The first index should be the like list and the second index should be the dislike list. A result of 1.0 means the two pairs of lists are exactly the same. A result of -1.0 means the two pairs of lists are completely opposite.
        Parameters:
        one - the first pair of lists
        two - the second pair of lists
        Returns:
        a decimal between -1 and 1, inclusive, that indicates the similarity

      • rankUsers

        private void rankUsers()
        Ranks the list of users based on their similarity to the known likes and dislikes. The list will be sorted in descending order.
